<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:46:19 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>层状晶体嵌入原子薄的硒化铁可以改善余热转化</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/layered-crystal-embeds-atom-thin-iron-selenide-can-improve-waste-heat-conversion</link><description>开发能够有效地将废热转化为电能的热电材料仍然具有挑战性，因为高电性能和低导热率很难同时实现。东京科学学院的研究人员开发出一种层状晶体 TlFe &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/layered-crystal-embeds-atom-thin-iron-selenide-can-improve-waste-heat-conversion2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:46:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/layered-crystal-embeds-atom-thin-iron-selenide-can-improve-waste-heat-conversion</guid></item><item><title>CMS 利用美丽介子探索微妙的物质与物质差异 CERN</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/cms-explores-subtle-matterantimatter-difference-using-beauty-mesons-cern</link><description>CMS实验使用迄今为止最大的美介子样本，对物质与反物质之间的细微差异进行高精度测试。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cms-explores-subtle-matterantimatter-difference-using-beauty-mesons-cern2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:31:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/cms-explores-subtle-matterantimatter-difference-using-beauty-mesons-cern</guid></item><item><title>新的成像方法可追踪从全身到单个细胞的癌症</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/new-imaging-method-tracks-cancer-from-whole-body-to-individual-cells</link><description>癌症研究中最大的挑战之一是将医学扫描中看到的“大局”与驱动肿瘤生长并决定患者对治疗如何反应的微观生物学联系起来。现在，通过结合多种成像技术（PET 扫描、生物发光和荧光），科学家可以同时检测整个身体的肿瘤，查明关键目标，然后详细检查这些肿瘤，包括周围的细胞和组织。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-imaging-method-tracks-cancer-from-whole-body-to-individual-cells2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:16:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/new-imaging-method-tracks-cancer-from-whole-body-to-individual-cells</guid></item><item><title>婴儿期的体力活动与三岁时的身体成分有关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/physical-activity-in-infancy-is-associated-with-body-composition-at-age-three</link><description>在包括遗传倾向以及产前和产后影响在内的多因素病因的推动下，儿科人群的肥胖患病率正在增加。我们的目的是探讨一岁和三岁时儿童体力活动 (PA) 与三岁时身体成分之间的关​​联。此外，我们还研究了怀孕期间母亲 PA 与三岁时儿童身体成分之间的关​​联。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/physical-activity-in-infancy-is-associated-with-body-composition-at-age-three.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:01:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/physical-activity-in-infancy-is-associated-with-body-composition-at-age-three</guid></item><item><title>唾液皮质醇与老年人认知能力下降和阿尔茨海默病</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/salivary-cortisol-and-cognitive-decline-and-alzheimer-disease-in-older-adults</link><description>这项队列研究探讨了每日唾液皮质醇指数是否与认知结果（包括阿尔茨海默病）相关，以及分布和关联是否因种族而异。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/salivary-cortisol-and-cognitive-decline-and-alzheimer-disease-in-older-adults.png" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 11:46:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/salivary-cortisol-and-cognitive-decline-and-alzheimer-disease-in-older-adults</guid></item><item><title>神经肌肉疾病的核仁观点</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/a-nucleolar-view-of-neuromuscular-disease</link><description>核仁是核糖体生物发生和细胞稳态的主要调节者，也是神经肌肉疾病日益重要的决定因素。在这些条件下，不同的遗传和分子损伤集中在核仁组织和功能的改变上。这些变化影响核糖体 RNA 合成并重塑翻译输出，将核事件与疾病相关环境中的细胞质蛋白稳态联系起来。在这篇综述中，我们提出了一个综合框架，其中核仁整合了 RNA 功能障碍、基因组组织和跨神经肌肉疾病的翻译控制。这一观点为解释疾病异质性提供了概念基础，并强调核仁通路作为潜在的、未充分开发的治疗干预目标。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-nucleolar-view-of-neuromuscular-disease2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 11:31:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/a-nucleolar-view-of-neuromuscular-disease</guid></item><item><title>恢复两小时睡眠：研究人员在阿尔茨海默病方面取得突破</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/two-hours-of-sleep-restored-researchers-make-alzheimers-breakthrough</link><description>你的厨房里有一个小火被隔离。如果你有合适的工具，你也许能够把它推出来。但在你之前，洒水装置就打开了，淹没了你的整个房子。对问题的自动响应现在已经损坏了您拥有的一切。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/two-hours-of-sleep-restored-researchers-make-alzheimers-breakthrough2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 11:16:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/two-hours-of-sleep-restored-researchers-make-alzheimers-breakthrough</guid></item><item><title>摘要：通讯地址：Carlos Carmona-Fontaine, New York University, Brown Building Of 760, 31 Washington Pl., New York, New York 10,003, USA</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/abstract-address-correspondence-to-carlos-carmona-fontaine-new-york-university-brown-building-of-760-31-washington-pl-new-york-new-york-10003-usa</link><description>电子邮件：&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/abstract158.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 11:01:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/abstract-address-correspondence-to-carlos-carmona-fontaine-new-york-university-brown-building-of-760-31-washington-pl-new-york-new-york-10003-usa</guid></item><item><title>结核分枝杆菌ClpP1P2蛋白酶及其相关ATP酶的激活机制和结构组装</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/activation-mechanism-and-structural-assembly-of-the-mycobacterium-tuberculosis-clpp1p2-protease-and-its-associated-atpases</link><description>温豪普尔等人。确定 ClpC1P1P2 复合物的冷冻电镜结构&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/activation-mechanism-and-structural-assembly-of-the-mycobacterium-tuberculosis-clpp1p2-protease-and-its-associated-atpases2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 10:46:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/activation-mechanism-and-structural-assembly-of-the-mycobacterium-tuberculosis-clpp1p2-protease-and-its-associated-atpases</guid></item><item><title>表观遗传编辑崭露头角</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/epigenetic-editing-makes-its-mark</link><description>研究人员正在重写 DNA 和染色质上的化学标签来调整基因表达。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/epigenetic-editing-makes-its-mark.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 10:31:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/epigenetic-editing-makes-its-mark</guid></item></channel></rss>